    "author_association": "CONTRIBUTOR",
    "body": "\"info\" error severity in Solidity [is colored with white](https://github.com/ethereum/solidity/blob/a297a687261a1c634551b1dac0e36d4573c19afe/liblangutil/SourceReferenceFormatter.cpp#L79) ([code 37](https://github.com/ethereum/solidity/blob/2f451a186b23bd2ec22c2a594b7cafa8a92e7597/libsolutil/AnsiColorized.h#L44)) so I just copied that from them ([ethers-rs](https://github.com/gakonst/ethers-rs/blob/df165b84229cdc1c65e8522e0c1aeead3746d9a8/ethers-solc/src/artifacts/mod.rs#L2165), definition is also [code 37](https://github.com/SergioBenitez/yansi/blob/fe19ffc988897d7848565477cee3d1a8e908458c/src/color.rs#L35-L36)).\r\nThis should be handled by your terminal, since I just tried myself and this displays just fine on either light or dark mode:\r\n\r\n```sh\r\nprintf '\\e[37mhello in white\\e[0m\\n\\e[37;1mhello in bold white\\e[0m\\n'\r\n```\r\n\r\nSee for example [wikipedia](https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/ANSI_escape_code#3-bit_and_4-bit), [`alacritty-theme`](https://github.com/alacritty/alacritty-theme)",
